import React, {useState} from 'react';
import Modal from 'react-bootstrap/Modal';
import Container from 'react-bootstrap/Container';
import Row from 'react-bootstrap/Row';
import enterpriseExpertiseImage from '../../images/01_EnEx.webp';
import missionExpertiseImage from '../../images/02_MiEx.webp';
import enterpriseTechnologyImage from '../../images/03_MnTe.webp';
import Col from 'react-bootstrap/Col';
import '../../App.css';
import './Pages.css';

export default function ExpertiseTechnology()
{
	const [modalCategory, setModalCategory] = useState(0);

	const [showModal, setShowModal] = useState(false);

	const enterpriseExpertiseContent = <Row><Col lg={6}><div className='columnTextInner'><p className='preHeader'>ENTERPRISE EXPERTISE</p><h3>Modernization At Scale</h3><p>CACI’s expert engineers, scientists, analysts, and professionals are critical to our ongoing growth and success. Their talents enable our customer operations and enterprise modernization goals.</p><p>In FY22, enterprise expertise remained vital to business growth, including several awards, such as CACI’s prime position on the six-year multiple-award, indefinite delivery/indefinite quantity (IDIQ) U.S. Navy’s Technical Support Services (TSS) contract, supporting Manpower, Personal, Training, and Equipment (MPT&E), with a ceiling value of $575 million. Under the contract, CACI will continue to provide enterprise expertise to ensure sailor readiness and implement a transformation of the Navy HR information system. CACI has supported MPT&E for more than 25 years and this award directly supports the Navy’s mission to attract, train, and retain highly qualified personnel.</p></div></Col><Col lg={6}><img src={enterpriseExpertiseImage} alt="Enterprise Expertise" width="100%" height="100%" /></Col></Row>;

	const missionExpertiseContent = <Row><Col lg={6}><div className='columnTextInner'><p className='preHeader'>MISSION EXPERTISE</p><h3>Understanding today’s needs to meet tomorrow’s demands</h3><p>CACI’s mission expertise continues to deliver the specialized talent, tacit knowledge, and technical training that empowers our customers to meet their missions.</p><p>Our technical and mission-critical expertise is well-recognized and well-received by our customers, such as the U.S Army Special Operations Command (USASOC), which awarded us with a five-year single-award task order worth up to $785 million. The award for Special Operations Forces Emerging Threats, Operations, and Planning Support (SOFETOPS), provides expertise in integrated information warfare (IW) and EW solutions, training, readiness, and modernization, to help USASOC adapt to both present and future threats.</p><p>CACI was named the prime contract awardee on all 10 pools on the General Services Administration (GSA) ASTRO IDIQ contract. This award provides mission-specific data operations, artificial intelligence, and life cycle support expertise, including sustainment and modernization and ISR. The GSA contract is an easy-to-use acquisition vehicle, through which CACI’s renowned talent will support the government to quickly address mission needs across all domains.</p><p>CACI is known for its strong partnerships with its customers, as is evident through its reception of the Defense Threat Reduction Agency’s (DTRA) Decisive Action task order. The single-award task order, valued at $1.4 billion, can largely be credited to CACI’s intimate understanding of DTRA’s mission, spanning more than 14 years. The task order continues and expands CACI’s previous work with DTRA, providing the agency with a wide range of analytical expertise that enables mission solutions to counter and deter multi-faceted threats. CACI’s strong understanding of current threats supports DTRA to combat adversarial networks and threats.</p><p>CACI’s mission experts also support U.S. Immigration and Customs Enforcement (ICE) under the department’s Tactical Communications task order. The TACCOM II program expands the scope and size of the company’s support to ICE, specifically providing development and maintenance activities for ICE’s critical voice communications capabilities.</p><p>By understanding the latest technological advances and possessing an equal intimacy with our customer’s mission needs, CACI knows how to best serve our customers and defend national security.</p></div></Col><Col lg={6}><img src={missionExpertiseImage} alt="Mission Expertise" width="100%" height="100%" /></Col></Row>;

